
1. Introduction
1.1 Purpose

The purpose of this Software Requirements Specification (SRS) document is to provide a detailed description of the requirements for the Predictive Stock Management System (PSMS). This document is intended to be submitted online as part of an academic/project deliverable and serves as a formal agreement between stakeholders, developers, and end users.

The SRS clearly defines the systemâ€™s functional and non-functional requirements, constraints, assumptions, and interfaces to ensure a shared understanding of the system before development begins.

1.2 Document Conventions

Shall indicates a mandatory requirement.

Should indicates a recommended requirement.

May indicates an optional requirement.

All headings follow IEEE SRS-style formatting for clarity and online submission.

1.3 Intended Audience and Reading Suggestions

This document is intended for:

Project supervisors and evaluators

System analysts and designers

Developers and testers

End users such as inventory managers and administrators

Readers unfamiliar with the system should begin with Sections 1 and 2 for an overview, while technical readers may focus on Sections 3 and 4.

1.4 Product Scope

The Predictive Stock Management System is designed to help organizations efficiently manage inventory by forecasting future stock requirements using historical sales data and predictive analytics. The system aims to:

Reduce overstocking and understocking

Improve demand forecasting accuracy

Automate stock alerts and reports

Support data-driven inventory decisions

1.5 References

IEEE 830-1998 Recommended Practice for Software Requirements Specifications

Inventory Management System Literature

Predictive Analytics and Forecasting Models Documentation

2. Overall Description
2.1 Product Perspective

The Predictive Stock Management System is a standalone, web-based application that can integrate with existing sales or ERP systems through APIs. It uses a centralized database and predictive algorithms to analyze historical stock and sales data.

2.2 Product Functions

Major functions of the system include:

User authentication and role management

Product and inventory management

Sales data collection and storage

Stock demand prediction

Alert generation for low or excess stock

Report generation and data visualization

2.3 User Classes and Characteristics

Administrator: Manages users, system settings, and overall inventory data.

Inventory Manager: Monitors stock levels, reviews predictions, and takes replenishment decisions.

Analyst (Optional): Reviews trends, forecasts, and reports for strategic planning.

Users are expected to have basic computer literacy and familiarity with inventory processes.

2.4 Operating Environment

Client: Web browser (Chrome, Firefox, Edge)

Server: Application server hosted on cloud or local infrastructure

Database: Relational database (MySQL/PostgreSQL)

Operating Systems: Windows, macOS, Linux

2.5 Design and Implementation Constraints

System must comply with data security and privacy standards

Predictions depend on the quality and availability of historical data

Internet connectivity required for web access

2.6 User Documentation

Online user manual

Help section within the application

Admin setup guide

2.7 Assumptions and Dependencies

Historical sales data is available and accurate

Users will input correct inventory updates

Predictive models rely on consistent data patterns

3. External Interface Requirements
3.1 User Interfaces

Login and authentication screens

Dashboard showing stock levels and predictions

Inventory management forms

Graphs and charts for trends and forecasts

Alerts and notification panels

The interface shall be responsive and user-friendly.

3.2 Hardware Interfaces

No specific hardware interfaces are required. The system shall run on standard computing devices.

3.3 Software Interfaces

Database Management System (DBMS)

Optional ERP or POS system APIs

Analytics and machine learning libraries

3.4 Communication Interfaces

HTTPS protocol for secure communication

RESTful APIs for data exchange

4. System Features
4.1 User Authentication and Authorization

Description: Allows users to securely log in and access features based on roles.

Functional Requirements:

The system shall authenticate users using username and password.

The system shall support role-based access control.

4.2 Inventory Management

Description: Enables adding, updating, and deleting product and stock details.

Functional Requirements:

The system shall allow users to add new products.

The system shall update stock quantities in real time.

4.3 Sales Data Management

Description: Stores and manages historical sales data for prediction.

Functional Requirements:

The system shall store daily sales records.

The system shall allow importing sales data.

4.4 Stock Prediction Module

Description: Predicts future stock demand using historical data.

Functional Requirements:

The system shall generate stock demand forecasts.

The system shall display predicted values graphically.

4.5 Alerts and Notifications

Description: Notifies users about low stock or excess inventory.

Functional Requirements:

The system shall generate alerts when stock falls below a threshold.

The system shall notify users via dashboard alerts.

4.6 Reporting and Analytics

Description: Generates reports for decision-making.

Functional Requirements:

The system shall generate inventory and forecast reports.

The system shall allow exporting reports in PDF/Excel format.

5. Non-Functional Requirements
5.1 Performance Requirements

The system shall handle multiple users simultaneously.

Predictions shall be generated within acceptable response time.

5.2 Security Requirements

The system shall encrypt sensitive data.

Only authorized users shall access system features.

5.3 Reliability Requirements

The system shall ensure data consistency and backup.

System uptime should be high during business hours.

5.4 Usability Requirements

The interface shall be intuitive and easy to use.

Minimal training should be required.

5.5 Scalability Requirements

The system shall support growth in data volume and users.

6. Other Requirements

Audit logs for critical operations

Configurable prediction thresholds

System configuration options for administrators

7. Future Enhancements

Integration with real-time POS systems

Advanced machine learning models

Mobile application support

Automated supplier ordering

8. Appendices
Appendix A: Glossary

